			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: mobs with weapons?<a name="35080"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 16 04 4:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Personally, I like to do the goblins in Solsek A.  Also, you can disarm when grouped and fighting.  Disarm is a mixed bag skill.  I am a 40 bard and 57 rogue, so you know where I am coming from.
<br />

<br />
Disarming a creature does not stop it from fighting.  The mob will go hand to hand without missing a beat.  Some of the intelligent mobs will cry out, &quot;My weapon!&quot; when disarmed (gnolls are famous for this).
<br />

<br />
The reason Disarm is a mixed bag is that the weapon dmg/dly ratio affects mobs just like it affects you.  If the mob is carry a dagger it might hit more frequently but for less damage.  If its carrying a morningstar it might hit less frequently but for more damage.  Some mobs it is best to leave them armed since unarmed fighting actually gives them better DPS.  Also, if the mob has a 2 handed weapon it probably won't get dual wield attacks (although it would get double attacks).  Nice to know if the mob tends to quad when unarmed.  
<br />

<br />
Honestly, once I max'd disarm with my rogue (in my low 40's) I stopped using it.  I had more important hot keys to fill in my slots.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
