				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: mobs with weapons?<a name="35126"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 16 04 10:39 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Try this. Get a rusty weapon and go out to say. East Commonlands. Find an orc. Give him the weapon. Then start hitting your disarm key. After the first disarm attempt the orc will be aggroed but he probably isn't gonna hurt you too much.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />  . Once you actually disarm him just kill him and grab the weapon off the ground. Rinse and repeat endlessly. Frankly there is really no point to disarm except it can give you a very maginal added aggro. This only works on mobs that will not aggro on you normally, ie very low greens. There is an old GU Comic about this. Shows a warrior handing a weapon to a gnoll and the gnoll looking confused and the warrior saying something like &quot;Well how else am I supposed to practice my disarm?&quot; Good stuff. 
<br />

<br />
Oh and I don't think mob damage is affected by weapons with the exception being if they are weilding a 2handed weapon they don't get their offhand attack. I am pretty sure this was done to prevent people from sneaking up to a mob and giving it rusty weapons to reduce it dps. I thought that was changed along time ago. Otherwise I would hate to see what a Diaku would hit for if given a real weapon instead of the crud they normally carry. 
<br />

<br />
And yes a mob has to have a weapon to get a skillup using disarm.</span></td>
